"35:44:11" : {s: 35, a: 44, w: 11, r: "قبل", t: "قَبْلِهِمْ", l: "قَبْل", lc: 242, tl: "qablihim", lb: "পূর্বে ",e: "(were) before them", b: "তাদের পূর্ববর্তীদের (মত)", f: 29, rm: "to accept/admit/receive/agree, meet anyone, to face/encounter someone/something, advance/approach, correspond, counteract/compare/requite/compensate, the front part (12:26), accept with approval, show favour."},
"35:44:12" : {s: 35, a: 44, w: 12, r: "كون", t: "وَكَانُوٓا۟", l: "كَانَ", lc: 1358, tl: "wakānū", lb: "হয়, হতো",e: "And they were", b: "এবং তারা ছিল", f: 32, rm: "To be, exist, happen, occur, take place, become, be such or so, originated."},
"35:44:13" : {s: 35, a: 44, w: 13, r: "شدد", t: "أَشَدَّ", l: "أَشَدّ", lc: 31, tl: "ashadda", lb: "কঠোর, অধিক শক্ত",e: "stronger", b: "অধিকতর", f: 9, rm: "to bind tightly, strap, strengthen firmly, run, establish, make firm, hard, strong, be advanced (day), be intense. ushdud - harden, strengthen. shadiid (pl. shidaad & ashiddau - great, firm, strict, vehement, strong, violent, severe, mighty, terrible, stern, grievous, miserly, niggardly. (adj. of the forms faiil and fiaal are used indifferently for both m. and f.): ashuddun: age of full strength, maturity. ishtadda (vb. 8) - to act with violence, become hard."},
"35:44:14" : {s: 35, a: 44, w: 14, r: "", t: "مِنْهُمْ", l: "مِن", lc: 3067, tl: "minhum", lb: "মধ্য থেকে, কিছুর চেয়ে",e: "than them", b: "তাদের মধ্য থেকে (তাদের কথা ভিন্ন)", f: 67, rm: ""},
"35:44:15" : {s: 35, a: 44, w: 15, r: "قوي", t: "قُوَّةًۭ", l: "قُوَّة", lc: 30, tl: "quwwatan", lb: "শক্তি",e: "(in) power", b: "শক্তিতে", f: 12, rm: "to be, become strong, prevail, be able to do, be powerful, be vigorous, be forceful. quwwatun (pl. quwan) - power, strength, vigour, resolution, firmness, determination. qawun - desert. aqwa - to stay in desert. muqwin - dwellers of desert/wilderness (it is derived from the verb qawiya which means: it became desolate or deserted)."},
"35:44:16" : {s: 35, a: 44, w: 16, r: "", t: "وَمَا", l: "مَا", lc: 2557, tl: "wama", lb: "না, যা, কী/কীসে?",e: "But not", b: "এবং যা", f: 646, rm: ""},
