"35:44:29" : {s: 35, a: 44, w: 29, r: "علم", t: "عَلِيمًۭا", l: "عَلِيم", lc: 163, tl: "ʿalīman", lb: "পরম জ্ঞানী ",e: "All-Knower", b: "মহাজ্ঞানী", f: 22, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows."},
